User Stories:
  - [X] As a user, I want to start a timer so that I can focus for a fixed period.
  - [X] As a user, I want to stop a timer so that I can pause work if needed.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to update the focus and break time so that the timer fits my schedule.
  - [X] As a user, I want to switch between Deep Work Mode and Break Time mode so that I can focus or relax appropriately.
  - [X] As a user, I want a notification when the timer ends so that I know when to switch tasks.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to create todos so that I can track my tasks.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to select a todo to work on so that I can focus on one task at a time.
  - [X] As a user, I want to see the current todo I’m working on so that I stay organized.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to edit a single todo so that I can update task details.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to remove a single todo so that I can declutter my list.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to mark a todo as completed so that I can track progress.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to prioritize tasks so that I focus on what matters most.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to add notes to a task so that I remember important details.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to remove all todos so that I can reset my list.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to remove only completed todos so that I keep my list tidy.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to reset all completed statuses and Pomodoro sessions so that I can start fresh.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to customize my username so that the app feels personal.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to choose alarm sounds so that notifications suit my preferences.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to switch color themes so that the interface is visually comfortable.
  - [ ] As a user, I want background sounds so that I feel more relaxed while working.
  - [ ] As a user, I want my todos, settings, and Pomodoro sessions saved so that I can retrieve them later.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to log in and see my saved data so that I can resume where I left off.
  - [ ] As a user, I want a weekly report so that I can review my daily focus time.
  - [ ] As a user, I want a monthly report so that I can analyze my weekly focus patterns.
  - [ ] As a user, I want a yearly report so that I can evaluate long-term trends.
  - [ ] As a user, I want project-specific reports so that I can assess time spent on different projects.
  - [ ] As a user, I want templates so that I can quickly add recurring tasks.
  - [ ] As a user, I want to integrate with Todoist Inbox so that I can sync my tasks.
  - [ ] As a user, I want keyboard shortcuts so that I can navigate the app faster.

Engineer Stories:
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want unit tests for core components so that I can ensure they work as expected.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want integration tests for features like the todo list so that user flows are reliable.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want end-to-end tests for the timer and notifications so that the app behaves correctly across scenarios.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want to use DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles so that the codebase is maintainable.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want modularized components so that features are reusable and scalable.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want clear folder structures for frontend, backend, and shared utilities so that the project is easy to navigate.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want to save user data (todos, settings, Pomodoro sessions) to Firebase so that data persists across sessions.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want to retrieve user data from Firebase when they log in so that their app state is restored.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want secure authentication for users so that only authorized users can access their data.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want to optimize database writes and reads to reduce latency and cost.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want to handle offline scenarios gracefully so that users can work without an internet connection and sync later.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want error handling for database operations so that users are informed if data fails to load or save.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want robust validation for todo inputs and settings so that invalid data doesn’t break the app.
  - [ ] As an engineer, I want to follow accessibility best practices so that the app is usable by all users.
